\subsection{Piece (i): sub-lemma decomposition for iter-128+ build}
\label{subsec:RigidityKbar_piece_i_decomposition}

We decompose piece (i) above into three sub-steps (i.a)\,$\to$\,(i.b)\,$\to$\,(i.c) that are well-suited to staged Lean formalisation. Sub-step (i.a) defines the Lie algebra (as a $k$-vector space) of a group scheme at the identity and pins its rank; sub-step (i.b) globalises that fibre across $G$ via a functorial shear isomorphism; sub-step (i.c) concludes the freeness and rank of the relative cotangent $\Omega_{G/k}$.

All three sub-steps are stated over an arbitrary base field $k$ per the iter-127 over-k commitment (see the chapter introduction, \S "Iter-127 over-k commitment"); the prose carefully avoids any reliance on $k$-rational or $\bar k$-rational point lifting, working functorially throughout. Sub-step (i.a) is the natural first target for the iter-128+ prover lane: it has the smallest signature surface (a finite-rank free $k$-module attached to the identity section of $G$), no scheme-level globalisation, and an exact rank value $\dim G$.

Throughout this subsection, $k$ is an arbitrary field and $G : \Over\,(\Spec k)$ is a smooth proper geometrically irreducible group scheme over $k$, with identity section $\eta_G : \mathbf{1} \to G$.

\begin{lemma}[(i.a) Lie algebra of a group scheme at the identity]
  \label{lem:GrpObj_lieAlgebra}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.GrpObj.lieAlgebra}
  \notready
  The pullback along the identity section $\eta_G$ of the relative cotangent presheaf,
  \[
    \mathfrak g^{\vee} \;:=\; \eta_G^{*}\,\Omega_{G/k},
  \]
  is a finitely generated free $k$-module. Its $k$-linear dual $\mathfrak g$ is the \emph{Lie algebra of $G$} as a $k$-vector space (the bracket structure is not used in the rigidity argument and is not packaged here).
\end{lemma}

\begin{proof}
  The identity section $\eta_G$ is a canonical $k$-rational point of $G$ supplied by the $\GrpObj$ structure. The pullback $\eta_G^{*}\,\Omega_{G/k}$ is, on evaluation at $\Spec k$, the cotangent space $\mathfrak m / \mathfrak m^{2}$ of the local ring $\mathcal O_{G, \eta_G}$ as a $k$-vector space, where $\mathfrak m$ is the maximal ideal at the identity. Smoothness of $G$ at $\eta_G$ makes the local ring regular; finite generation and freeness of $\mathfrak m / \mathfrak m^{2}$ as a $k$-vector space follow from regularity. The $k$-linear dual $\mathfrak g$ inherits the same finite-rank-free structure.
\end{proof}

\begin{lemma}[(i.a) Rank of the Lie algebra]
  \label{lem:GrpObj_lieAlgebra_finrank}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.GrpObj.lieAlgebra_finrank_eq_dim}
  \uses{lem:GrpObj_lieAlgebra}
  \notready
  In the setting of \cref{lem:GrpObj_lieAlgebra},
  \[
    \finrank_{k}\,\mathfrak g \;=\; \finrank_{k}\,\mathfrak g^{\vee} \;=\; \dim G.
  \]
\end{lemma}

\begin{proof}
  \uses{lem:GrpObj_lieAlgebra}
  The cotangent space at a smooth point of a $d$-dimensional scheme is a $d$-dimensional $k$-vector space; here $d = \dim_{\eta_G} G = \dim G$, since the local dimension at the identity agrees with the global dimension when $G$ is geometrically irreducible. The rank of a finitely generated free $k$-module agrees with the rank of its $k$-linear dual.
\end{proof}

\begin{lemma}[(i.b) Shear-iso globalisation of the cotangent]
  \label{lem:GrpObj_mulRight_globalises}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.GrpObj.mulRight_globalises_cotangent}
  \uses{lem:GrpObj_lieAlgebra}
  \notready
  Let $\mu \colon G \times_{k} G \to G$ denote the multiplication of $G$ and let $\sigma \colon G \times_{k} G \to G \times_{k} G$ be the \emph{shear isomorphism}
  \[
    \sigma \;=\; \langle \pr_{1},\, \mu \rangle, \qquad (a, b) \;\mapsto\; (a,\, a \cdot b),
  \]
  built categorically from $\mu$ and the binary-product projections in $\Over\,(\Spec k)$. Then $\sigma$ is an isomorphism over the first projection, and pullback along $\sigma$ together with the canonical first-projection-cotangent identification $\Omega_{(G \times_{k} G)/G} \cong \pr_{2}^{*}\,\Omega_{G/k}$ yields a natural isomorphism
  \[
    \Omega_{G/k} \;\cong\; \pr_{1}^{*}\!\bigl(\eta_{G}^{*}\,\Omega_{G/k}\bigr) \qquad \text{on } G,
  \]
  i.e.\ the relative cotangent of $G$ is canonically isomorphic to the constant $\mathcal O_{G}$-module with fibre $\mathfrak g^{\vee}$ trivialised along the structure map $G \to \Spec k$.

  \paragraph{Iter-127 over-k risk register.} The globalisation \textbf{must} be formulated functorially via the shear scheme map $\sigma$ — which is a morphism in $\Over\,(\Spec k)$, valid for any base field — and \textbf{not} as a pointwise translation by closed (or $\bar k$-rational) points of $G$. The pointwise-translation argument requires either alg-closure of $k$ or a Nullstellensatz-style $\bar k$-point lifting (as in Mathlib's \texttt{pointEquivClosedPoint}, used in the alg-closed-base branch of \texttt{Mathlib.AlgebraicGeometry.Group.Smooth}); the functorial shear formulation sidesteps that obstacle entirely.
\end{lemma}

\begin{proof}
  \uses{lem:GrpObj_lieAlgebra}
  Build $\sigma = \langle \pr_{1}, \mu \rangle$ in $\Over\,(\Spec k)$ from the $\GrpObj$ data only. The candidate inverse
  \[
    \tau \;=\; \langle \pr_{1},\, \mu \circ (\iota \times \mathrm{id}_{G}) \rangle, \qquad (a, b) \;\mapsto\; (a,\, a^{-1} \cdot b),
  \]
  where $\iota$ is the inverse on $G$, is again a scheme map in $\Over\,(\Spec k)$. One verifies $\sigma \circ \tau = \mathrm{id}_{G \times_{k} G} = \tau \circ \sigma$ using the $\GrpObj$ axioms (associativity and left-inverse). With $\sigma$ an isomorphism, pullback identifies the relative cotangent for the first projection. Restriction along the section $\langle \mathrm{id}_{G},\, \eta_{G} \rangle \colon G \to G \times_{k} G$ evaluates the second-coordinate cotangent at $\eta_{G}$, yielding the displayed isomorphism. The construction relies only on $\GrpObj$ scheme maps and the existing $\GrpObj.\mathtt{mulRight}$ infrastructure of \texttt{Mathlib.AlgebraicGeometry.Group.Smooth} (\texttt{b80f227}, lines 50--51); no point-set translation enters.
\end{proof}

\begin{lemma}[(i.c) Freeness of the relative cotangent of $G$]
  \label{lem:GrpObj_omega_free}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.GrpObj.omega_free}
  \uses{lem:GrpObj_lieAlgebra, lem:GrpObj_mulRight_globalises}
  \notready
  The relative cotangent presheaf $\Omega_{G/k}$ is a free $\mathcal O_{G}$-module.
\end{lemma>

\begin{proof}
  \uses{lem:GrpObj_lieAlgebra, lem:GrpObj_mulRight_globalises}
  By \cref{lem:GrpObj_mulRight_globalises}, $\Omega_{G/k}$ is canonically isomorphic to the pullback along the structure map $G \to \Spec k$ of the $k$-vector space $\mathfrak g^{\vee} = \eta_{G}^{*}\,\Omega_{G/k}$. By \cref{lem:GrpObj_lieAlgebra}, $\mathfrak g^{\vee}$ is a finitely generated free $k$-module. The pullback of a finitely generated free $k$-module along the structure morphism is a finitely generated free $\mathcal O_{G}$-module.
\end{proof}

\begin{lemma}[(i.c) Rank of the relative cotangent of $G$]
  \label{lem:GrpObj_omega_rank_eq_dim}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.GrpObj.omega_rank_eq_dim}
  \uses{lem:GrpObj_omega_free, lem:GrpObj_lieAlgebra_finrank}
  \notready
  The (constant) rank of $\Omega_{G/k}$ as a free $\mathcal O_{G}$-module equals $\dim G$.
\end{lemma}

\begin{proof}
  \uses{lem:GrpObj_omega_free, lem:GrpObj_lieAlgebra_finrank}
  The rank of the pulled-back bundle equals the $k$-dimension of its fibre. The fibre is $\mathfrak g^{\vee}$, whose $k$-rank equals $\dim G$ by \cref{lem:GrpObj_lieAlgebra_finrank}.
\end{proof}

\begin{remark}
  \label{rem:piece_i_first_target}
  \uses{lem:GrpObj_lieAlgebra, lem:GrpObj_lieAlgebra_finrank}
  Sub-step (i.a) --- \cref{lem:GrpObj_lieAlgebra} together with \cref{lem:GrpObj_lieAlgebra_finrank} --- is the natural first target for the iter-128+ prover lane: it has the smallest signature surface among the three sub-steps (a $k$-vector-space-of-rank-$\dim G$ claim about the cotangent at the identity, with no scheme-level globalisation yet engaged) and pins an exact rank value $\dim G$. Sub-steps (i.b) and (i.c) are staged on top of (i.a) and may be dispatched to separate prover lanes once the (i.a) signature has landed.
\end{remark}

\textbf{Honest pile cost (pieces (i)+(ii)+(iii), piece (iv) deferred): 1350--2600 LOC over 7--14 iters.}

